magic potion.

34:48.462 --> 34:50.921
Makes it look 200 years old.

34:50.964 --> 34:52.964
<i> Fine details really show up</i>
<i> in the end,</i>

34:53.008 --> 34:55.592
so it's tedious,
it takes a lot of time,

34:55.636 --> 34:59.554
<i>but I think my skills show that</i>
<i> I'm ready for any challenge.</i>

34:59.598 --> 35:02.015
[grunts]

35:02.059 --> 35:04.893
Yep, she's sharp.

35:04.937 --> 35:07.521
Just keep on going.

35:07.564 --> 35:11.399
<i> - Last day,</i>
<i> and I'm quenching a new blade.</i>

35:11.443 --> 35:13.527
If I don't get this right
the first time,

35:13.570 --> 35:16.113
<i> I won't have enough time</i>
<i> to finish it.</i>

35:16.156 --> 35:19.241
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

35:19.284 --> 35:20.742
Well, no pings.

35:20.786 --> 35:22.119
Slap a handle on it
and call it good.

35:22.162 --> 35:24.162
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:24.206 --> 35:27.040
<i> I have no idea how</i>
<i> I'm gonna finish this handle.</i>

35:27.084 --> 35:28.917
<i> I think I'm just gonna go</i>
<i> as fast as I can,</i>

35:28.961 --> 35:31.545
<i> but this D-guard</i>
<i> is completely new to me.</i>

35:31.588 --> 35:33.421
I'm just gonna have
to make it up as I go along.

35:33.465 --> 35:35.507
<i> Worst-case scenario,</i>
<i> I just make something ugly.</i>

35:35.551 --> 35:38.260
Hmm.
Seriously no<i> bueno</i> here.

35:38.303 --> 35:40.345
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:40.389 --> 35:42.097
Go, damn it.
Be a handle.

35:42.141 --> 35:44.474
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:44.518 --> 35:46.143
<i> Not a piece of art,</i>

35:46.186 --> 35:49.479
but it's an instrument
of destruction.

35:49.523 --> 35:53.066
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:53.110 --> 35:54.568
- Welcome back, bladesmiths.

35:54.611 --> 35:56.319
We have some difficult
challenges

35:56.363 --> 35:59.072
for your blades today,
but before we get into that,

35:59.116 --> 36:02.075
David, how did it go
at the home forge?

36:02.119 --> 36:03.910
- I had issues with the time.

36:03.954 --> 36:06.872
<i> My first blade went great--</i>
<i> went to correct a bend,</i>

36:06.915 --> 36:08.832
<i> broke it,</i>
<i> had to start over.</i>

36:08.876 --> 36:10.917
<i> Considering what all</i>
<i> went wrong,</i>

36:10.961 --> 36:12.335
I'm happy with the way
it turned out.

36:12.379 --> 36:14.212
- Great.
Todd, how did it go

36:14.256 --> 36:15.589
for you at your home forge?

36:15.632 --> 36:17.507
- I had a little bit
of difficulty.

36:17.551 --> 36:19.509
<i> I use a coal forge,</i>
<i> and when you use a coal forge,</i>

36:19.553 --> 36:20.927
<i> you can't really</i>
<i> see the blade,</i>

36:20.971 --> 36:23.263
<i> and it burnt a couple places,</i>

36:23.307 --> 36:26.224
so I had to make another blade
and it came out great.

36:26.268 --> 36:27.809
- All right, well,
we're gonna find out

36:27.853 --> 36:29.394
because we're about to put
your weapons

36:29.438 --> 36:30.979
through a series of tests.

36:31.023 --> 36:34.816
Up first is the sharpness test.
Dave?

36:34.860 --> 36:37.152
- The cavalry saber was a weapon
that dominated

36:37.196 --> 36:39.237
the battlefields of Europe
for almost 200 years.

36:39.281 --> 36:41.031
So to test the sharpness
of your blades,

36:41.074 --> 36:43.200
I'm gonna take three cuts
against our bag here.

36:43.243 --> 36:44.534
Now, Dave, you're up first.
Are you ready?

36:44.578 --> 36:46.536
- Let's do it.

36:46.580 --> 36:48.997
I finally get to see
somebody use this thing.

36:49.041 --> 36:51.791
I am just so excited
to see what happens.

36:51.835 --> 36:54.669
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

36:54.713 --> 36:57.088
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:00.177 --> 37:02.636
- Went about 3/4 of the way
through.

37:02.679 --> 37:04.554
The curvature
of your weapon

37:04.598 --> 37:06.348
and the fact that it is
as sharp as it is

37:06.391 --> 37:08.516
really did a nice job
on that.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.185
Interesting-shaped guard,

37:10.229 --> 37:12.479
but to quote
a friend of mine,

37:12.522 --> 37:14.773
this will cut.

37:14.816 --> 37:16.358
All right, Todd, you're up.
Are you ready?

37:16.401 --> 37:17.859
- Yes, sir, I'm ready.

37:17.903 --> 37:19.945
Dave's sword slashes the bag,

37:19.988 --> 37:21.404
<i> so I'm feeling</i>
<i> a little anxious.</i>

37:21.448 --> 37:23.156
<i> We'll see what happens.</i>

37:23.200 --> 37:26.076
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

37:26.119 --> 37:30.830
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:30.874 --> 37:32.582
- All right, Todd,
right off the bat,

37:32.626 --> 37:35.752
I got a bit of a loose handle
right there.

37:35.796 --> 37:38.171
You can see that it
cut the bag nicely.

37:38.215 --> 37:40.507
It is sharp,
and it will cut.

37:40.550 --> 37:43.426
So well done on that.

37:43.470 --> 37:45.428
Next up
is our kill test.

37:45.472 --> 37:48.640
And for that,
I'll throw you over to Doug.

37:48.684 --> 37:51.434
- Bladesmiths, to see what kind
of lethal damage

37:51.478 --> 37:53.270
your saber can do,

37:53.313 --> 37:55.272
I will take your sword
and deliver multiple strikes

37:55.315 --> 37:56.815
on the ballistics dummy.

37:56.858 --> 37:58.316
Dave, you're up first.
Are you ready?

37:58.360 --> 38:00.610
- Let's kill that dummy.
- Let's do it.

38:00.654 --> 38:03.571
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

38:03.615 --> 38:10.537
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:16.628 --> 38:19.879
- Dave,
your blade is razor sharp.

38:19.923 --> 38:21.548
On the initial slash,
you can see

38:21.591 --> 38:23.591
how much it lacerated through.

38:23.635 --> 38:26.136
Second one made it all the way
into the bone,

38:26.179 --> 38:29.389
and even on the thrust, with
the way your blade is angled,

38:29.433 --> 38:32.058
you can lacerate and gut
everything that's in there.

38:32.102 --> 38:35.145
This, sir, will kill.
Good job.

38:35.188 --> 38:36.604
- Awesome, thank you.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.023
- Todd, you're up next.
Are you ready?

38:38.066 --> 38:39.691
- Yep.
- Let's do this.

38:39.735 --> 38:42.652
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

38:42.696 --> 38:49.576
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:53.540 --> 38:57.500
Okay, Todd, on the horizontal
slash with the movement,

38:57.544 --> 38:59.377
it dug in nicely.

38:59.421 --> 39:01.379
You've got a good configuration
with your blade here.

39:01.423 --> 39:03.882
This weapon will kill.

39:03.925 --> 39:05.008
- Awesome.
- Good job.

39:05.052 --> 39:06.468
- Thank you.

39:06.511 --> 39:07.927
- Next up
is the strength test.

39:07.971 --> 39:09.596
For that,
I'll throw you over to Dave.

39:09.639 --> 39:12.640
- Gentlemen,
to test the edge of your blade,

39:12.684 --> 39:15.310
we're gonna take your swords,
clamp them in a vise

39:15.354 --> 39:16.686
and fire a bullet at them.

39:16.730 --> 39:18.730
- Awesome.
- Dave, you're up.

39:18.774 --> 39:20.482
- What it takes to pass
a bullet test

39:20.525 --> 39:23.610
is, basically,
you just can't be over-hard.

39:23.653 --> 39:26.321
If you're over-hard,
you'll chip out or you'll break.

39:26.365 --> 39:28.281
<i> This is intense.</i>

39:28.325 --> 39:31.534
- Three, two, one.
Fire.

39:31.578 --> 39:33.453
[gunshot]

39:40.379 --> 39:42.087
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

39:42.130 --> 39:45.215
- Gentlemen,
to test the edge of your blade,

39:45.258 --> 39:47.675
we're gonna take your swords,
clamp them in a vise,

39:47.719 --> 39:49.177
and fire a bullet at them.

39:49.221 --> 39:51.137
- Awesome.
- Dave, you're up.

39:51.181 --> 39:52.555
- Tear it up.

39:52.599 --> 39:54.474
- All right, guys.

39:54.518 --> 39:58.019
Three, two, one.
Fire.

39:58.063 --> 39:59.813
[gunshot]

39:59.856 --> 40:01.773
- Yep, split it.

40:01.817 --> 40:04.567
- I'm just super relieved
when I see those three holes

40:04.611 --> 40:08.196
<i> appear in the backdrop.</i>

40:08.240 --> 40:11.157
- Dave, you can actually see
the two points

40:11.201 --> 40:13.743
where the hollow-point bullet
hit this blade.

40:13.787 --> 40:16.788
Other than that small deflection
right there,

40:16.832 --> 40:19.499
blade's held up nicely.
- Sweet.

40:19.543 --> 40:20.959
- All right, Todd.
Are you ready for this?

40:21.002 --> 40:22.794
- Yes, sir.

40:22.838 --> 40:24.462
Now, I'm pretty confident
the edge will hold up.

40:24.506 --> 40:26.923
I pre-tested it,
so we'll just wait and see

40:26.967 --> 40:28.383
what the bullet does.

40:28.427 --> 40:29.843
- All right, gentlemen.

40:29.886 --> 40:33.555
In three, two, one.

40:33.598 --> 40:34.848
Fire.

40:34.891 --> 40:36.433
[gunshot]

40:36.476 --> 40:38.268
Oh, yeah.
That split.

40:38.311 --> 40:39.769
[gunshot]

40:39.813 --> 40:45.108
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:45.152 --> 40:48.027
So that bullet split nicely
on your sword.

40:48.071 --> 40:49.863
There's a little bit
of edge deflection

40:49.906 --> 40:52.157
but very little.
Still straight.

40:52.200 --> 40:54.534
Hardly affected the edge
at all.

40:54.578 --> 40:57.162
Nicely done.
- Thank you.

40:57.205 --> 40:58.580
- All right, bladesmiths,

40:58.623 --> 41:00.582
our weapons tests
are now complete.

41:00.625 --> 41:02.625
From here, we'll reconvene
back at the Forge

41:02.669 --> 41:04.502
where the judges will make
a final decision

41:04.546 --> 41:06.754
about which one of you will be
"Forged in Fire" champion

41:06.798 --> 41:08.715
and leave with that check
for 10 grand.

41:08.758 --> 41:10.049
Thank you.

41:12.888 --> 41:16.097
Dave, Todd, the judges
have made their final decision.

41:16.141 --> 41:19.100
But before that, they have
feedback for both of you.

41:19.144 --> 41:21.311
Jason.
- David,

41:21.354 --> 41:23.605
what I really appreciated
about yours

41:23.648 --> 41:26.900
<i>was its ability to nearly slice</i>
<i> through that bag.</i>

41:26.943 --> 41:29.110
Incredibly sharp.
Well done.

41:29.154 --> 41:31.863
- Thank you, sir.
- Doug.

41:31.907 --> 41:35.033
- Todd, I really like
the profile of your saber.

41:35.076 --> 41:36.659
<i> In the kill test, I really</i>
<i> enjoyed the way</i>

41:36.703 --> 41:39.746
<i> your blade was designed</i>
<i> to thrust.</i>

41:39.789 --> 41:41.706
Did a lot of damage.
Good job.

41:41.750 --> 41:43.750
- Thank you.

41:43.793 --> 41:46.669
- All right, gentlemen,
you've both done fantastic work.

41:46.713 --> 41:49.005
However, in this arena
of competition,

41:49.049 --> 41:51.382
there can only be one
"Forged in Fire" champion.

41:51.426 --> 41:54.302
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

41:54.346 --> 41:55.887
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:55.931 --> 41:57.847
Dave...
congratulations.

41:57.891 --> 42:00.016
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion.

42:00.060 --> 42:03.394
Todd, your weapon
did not make the cut.

42:03.438 --> 42:04.896
David will explain.

42:04.940 --> 42:06.981
- Todd, what this eventually
came down to

42:07.025 --> 42:09.400
was a construction problem
with your handle.

42:09.444 --> 42:12.695
<i> The tang was so small,</i>
<i> the handle almost round.</i>

42:12.739 --> 42:14.697
Nothing was fitted up
tightly.

42:14.741 --> 42:16.199
So when I was
making the cuts,

42:16.243 --> 42:17.992
it was incredibly hard
to control.

42:18.036 --> 42:20.828
And because of that,
we're gonna have to let you go.

42:20.872 --> 42:24.666
- Todd, please surrender
your weapon.

42:24.709 --> 42:26.167
<i> - I'm very proud of what</i>
<i> I've done.</i>

42:26.211 --> 42:27.877
<i> To make a blade,</i>
<i> it doesn't matter</i>

42:27.921 --> 42:30.255
whether you've made 100
or 1,

42:30.298 --> 42:32.715
<i> things can happen at any time</i>
<i> just like life.</i>

42:32.759 --> 42:35.218
I'm just gonna move on,
you know, and do better

42:35.262 --> 42:39.472
and continue to make what I make
and do what I do.

42:39.516 --> 42:41.891
- Dave, congratulations.

42:41.935 --> 42:44.310
You are the new
"Forged in Fire" champion

42:44.354 --> 42:46.062
and will receive a check
for $10,000.

42:46.106 --> 42:47.689
Good job.
- Thank you.

42:47.732 --> 42:49.774
<i> I'm in total shock</i>
<i> over this.</i>

42:49.818 --> 42:51.734
I don't think any of this
is gonna sink in

42:51.778 --> 42:55.280
<i> until my feet touch down</i>
<i> in Oklahoma again.</i>

42:55.323 --> 42:58.783
I'm a hobbyist against a bunch
of full-time bladesmiths.

42:58.827 --> 43:01.160
<i> I'm gonna be talking forever</i>
<i> about this.</i>

43:01.204 --> 43:03.246
I'm very happy and excited.

